item.title: [HIVE-20733] GenericUDFOPEqualNS may not use = in plan descriptions
item.description:
right now GenericUDFOPEqualNS is displayed a "=" in explains; however it should be "<=>"....
this may cause some confusion...

related qtest: is_distinct_from.q

same: GenericUDFOPNotEqualNS
item.summary: GenericUDFOPEqualNS may not use = in plan descriptions

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: As discussed, instead of "<=>" I'll use "IS NOT DISTINCT FROM", as that matches the SQL Standards.
